freenet.node
Class SendableRequest

java.lang.Object
  freenet.node.SendableRequest
All Implemented Interfaces:
RandomGrabArrayItem
Direct Known Subclasses:
BaseSendableGet, SendableInsert
public abstract class SendableRequest
extends Object
implements RandomGrabArrayItem

A low-level request which can be sent immediately. These are registered on the ClientRequestScheduler. LOCKING: Because some subclasses may do wierd things like locking on an external object (see e.g. SplitFileFetcherSubSegment), if we do take the lock we need to do it last i.e. not call any subclass methods inside it.

public abstract SendableRequestItem chooseKey(KeysFetchingLocally keys,
                                              com.db4o.ObjectContainer container,
                                              ClientContext context)
Choose a key to fetch. Removes the block number from any internal queues (but not the key itself, implementors must have a separate queue of block numbers and mapping of block numbers to keys).

Returns:
An object identifying a specific key. null indicates no keys available.

isCancelled

public abstract boolean isCancelled(com.db4o.ObjectContainer container)
If true, the request has been cancelled, or has completed, either way it need not be registered any more. isEmpty() on the other hand means there are no queued blocks.

getClient

public abstract RequestClient getClient(com.db4o.ObjectContainer container)
Get client context object. This isn't called as frequently as you might expect - once on registration, and then when there is an error. So it doesn't need to be stored on the request itself, hence we pass in a container.
